<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,258,1111]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,978,1003]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1959" box="[700,830,978,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bradleyi">
<emphasis box="[700,830,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. bradleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the head as long as wide; the clypeus protruding and truncate with the clypeal carina angled; the frontal angle of the ocellar triangle obtuse; and the notaulus very narrow, whereas 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1959" box="[501,626,1050,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bradleyi">
<emphasis box="[501,626,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. bradleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the head long; the clypeus with the median lobe rounded and short; and the frontal angle of the ocellae forming a right angle.
</paragraph>
